    <abstract>
      <t>TWAMP can be used to measure the performance of end-to-end paths in networks. STAMP [rfc8762] and TWAMP light are more lightweight measurement methods. In the SRv6 network, it is also necessary to measure the performance of SRv6 policy. This document describes a method to measure srv6 policy through stamp and TWAMP light.</t>
